<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-31T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-31T08:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/314:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-31T15:00:00+02:00">January 31, 1934—3
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 31—10:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>10. The Foreign Office notified this Legation this morning of the
                                intention of the Government to expel Insull at the termination of
                                his <hi rend="italic">permit de séjour</hi> which expires tonight
                                and asked that he be furnished <pb facs="0667" n="567" xml:id="pg_567"/> with a valid passport to effect this
                                expulsion. I therefore request immediate revalidation of his
                                passport according to your telegram No. 58, November 22, 3 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d463fn27"><ref target="frus1933v02#pg_568"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1933, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 568</ref>.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>